Violent hail storms killed at least six tourists in northern Greece late on Wednesday, police said. A Czech couple died when strong winds blew their caravan away while a Russian man and his son were killed by a falling tree, they added. Debris from a building killed a woman from Romania. ERT television said the region of Halkidiki, near the city of Thessaloniki, was declared a state of emergency and that the minister for citizen protection, Michalis Chryssohoidis, went to observe the rescue operation on Wednesday evening. Fierce storms hit Greece, killing six foreign nationals Six foreign nationals, including two children, were killed and more than 100 other people injured after gale-force winds, rain and hailstorms struck Halkidiki in northern Greece late on Wednesday, uprooting trees and collapsing roofs, authorities sai Temperatures in Greece have reached 37Â°C in the past two days, and the country was hit on Wednesday night by violent hail storms and gusts of wind, particularly in the north. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 